Court finds State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing hearing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.

AS TO COUNT 1:
The court sentenced the defendant to 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction (CONCURRENT TO COUNT 2), with credit for 5 DAYS time served.  

AS TO COUNT 2:
The court sentenced the defendant to 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction (CONCURRENT TO COUNT 1), with credit for 5 DAYS time served.  

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:
Court STAYED sentences and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 MONTHS. Defendant can complete probation early at the discretion of the agent.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-Any programming completed with CHIPS to apply;
-Serve 15 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time (as to COUNT 1), STAYED pending review;
-A course in anger management;
-Mental health evaluation, comply with recommended treatment;
-Parenting classes;
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent;
-Absolute sobriety;
-No contact with victim I.Z.J. except as authorized by CHIPS and DMCPS;
-Cooperate with CHIPS and DMCPS;
-No corporal punishment of any kind;
-No contact with firearms;
-Provide DNA sample;
-Court WAIVES all non-mandatory court costs and fees;
-Pay all supervision fees, court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA surcharge during period of probation.  Unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment.

Defendant to report to probation and provide DNA sample by 7/18/2022.

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.

Filed: 
Memorandum of Conditions of Probation.

Agent to request probation review hearing with the Court, if it is needed.
